      <bioghist id="aspace_dfe2c44aaf4e21cb5854026c92531ce6">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Jared Eliot Association was a literary society founded in 1934. It was named after Jared Eliot, who graduated from Yale College in 1706 and was made a trustee in 1730.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_4422c8f1ae013bfe25e202fd50ceec89">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of correspondence, clippings, minutes of meetings, a scrapbook, questionnaires, exhibition materials, published materials, and notes documenting the Jared Eliot Association, with an emphasis on its "Great Books" exhibition.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
